OL,7,FGuernsey's health board has confirmed
OL,8,Fat least one resident has died as a
OL,9,Fresult of receiving infected blood.
OL,11,FDeputy Queripel Pursuant asked the
OL,12,FHealth and Social Care (HSC) Committee
OL,13,Fhow many islanders were victims of the
OL,14,Finfected blood scandal, and if any had
OL,15,Fdied as a result of receiving
OL,16,Fcontaminated blood.
OL,18,FHSC said it was aware of fewer than
OL,19,Ften victims of the scandal, with at
OL,20,Fleast one to four deaths recorded.
